SLS 26RS-999 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 32
BY SENATOR JACKSON-ANDREWS
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH. Commends the members of the Louisiana Athletic
Trainers Association for their dedicated hard work on behalf of the athletes of Louisiana and
designates March 24th as Louisiana Athletic Trainers Association day at the Louisiana State
Capitol.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend the members of the Louisiana Athletic Trainers Association (LATA) for their
3 dedicated hard work on behalf of the athletes of Louisiana and to designate March
4 24, 2026, as LATA Day at the Louisiana State Capitol.
5 WHEREAS, Louisiana Athletic Trainers Association members are skilled healthcare
6 professionals trained in the prevention, emergency management, evaluation, and therapeutic
7 intervention of sports-related injuries and conditions; and
8 WHEREAS, the mission statement of the national association is to represent, engage,
9 and foster the continued growth and development of the athletic training profession and
10 athletic trainers as unique healthcare providers; and
11 WHEREAS, athletic training is an allied healthcare profession recognized by the
12 American Medical Association, and certification in the profession requires strict educational
13 standards based on specific knowledge and skills; certified athletic trainers have a long
14 history of providing quality healthcare for athletes and individuals engaged in physical
15 activity; and
16 WHEREAS, the hard work of the men and women of the LATA has allowed citizens
17 of Louisiana to participate in meaningful and rewarding athletic competitions throughout the
18 state and nation.
